text.tspan: G & Miettinen. From Black and White to Full Colour: Extending Redescription Mining
Outside the Boolean World. In SDM, pages 546–557,2011.
Soberón & Peterson. Interpretation of models of fundamental ecological niches and
Redescription mining is a powerful data analysis tool that aims at
finding alternative descriptions the same entities. For example,
in biology, an important task is to identify the bioclimatic
constraints that allow some species to survive, that is, to describe
geographical regions in terms of both their bioclimatic conditions
and the fauna that inhabits them. When the entities are geographic
locations, we qualify the redescriptions as geospatial. Using Siren,
a user can explore data of his interest by visualizing geospatial
redescriptions on a map, interactively edit, expand and filter them.
